  "texts": [
    "In the GraphSynergy model (Yang et al. 2021), a GCN is employed, specially tailored to understand the connections between drugs and disease modules within this network.",
    "MOOMIN (Rozemberczki et al. 2022) learns drug representations by encoding properties of compounds and sequence proteins into vertex features.",
    "Similarly, SDCNet (Zhang et al. 2022a) applies GCN with attention layers to get relevant details from the drug-cell line network, creating important features.",
    "The framework of the DTSyn model consists of two paths: a fine-grained block and a coarse-grained block.",
    "To use GCN, input chemical features are processed through GCN blocks and combined with gene embeddings."
